<subSubSection box="[189,1052,1944,1971]" pageId="13" pageNumber="204" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[136,1452,1944,2079]" box="[189,1052,1944,1971]" pageId="13" pageNumber="204">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,328,1944,1970]" pageId="13" pageNumber="204">Etymology:</emphasis>
—The specific epithet is derived from its 
<typeStatus box="[795,843,1945,1971]" pageId="13" pageNumber="204">type</typeStatus>
locality, Lhozhag.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="205" pageId="13" pageNumber="204" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[136,1452,1944,2079]" lastBlockId="14.[136,1452,158,437]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="205" pageId="13" pageNumber="204">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,315,1980,2006]" pageId="13" pageNumber="204">Discussion</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. S. Chen" authorityYear="2014" box="[351,614,1980,2007]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="13" pageNumber="204" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lhozhagensis">
<emphasis box="[351,614,1980,2007]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="204">Saussurea lhozhagensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
obviously belongs to 
<emphasis box="[850,864,1981,2007]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="204">S</emphasis>
. subgen. 
<taxonomicName box="[966,1092,1981,2006]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="13" pageNumber="206" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Eriocoryne">
<emphasis box="[966,1092,1981,2006]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="204">Eriocoryne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because its capitula are clustered in densely congested hemispheric synflorescences surrounded by densely lanate leaves. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. S. Chen" authorityYear="2014" box="[1154,1423,2016,2043]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="13" pageNumber="204" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lhozhagensis">
<emphasis box="[1154,1423,2016,2043]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="204">Saussurea lhozhagensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Liu 1984: 69) Fujikawa &amp; Ohba (2010: 73)" authorityName="Fujikawa &amp; Ohba" authorityPageNumber="73" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Liu" baseAuthorityPageNumber="69" baseAuthorityYear="1984" box="[256,923,2052,2079]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="13" pageNumber="204" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="conaensis">
<emphasis box="[256,397,2053,2079]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="204">S. conaensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Liu, S. W." box="[415,568,2052,2079]" pageId="13" pageNumber="204" pagination="55 - 71" refId="ref7460" refString="Liu, S. W. (1984) New taxa of Compositae from Xizang (Tibet). Acta Biologica Plateau Sinica 3: 55 - 71." type="journal article" year="1984">Liu 1984: 69</bibRefCitation>
) Fujikawa &amp; Ohba (2010: 73)
</taxonomicName>
in its leaf shape and naked receptacle, but 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. S. Chen" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="205" order="Asterales" pageId="13" pageNumber="204" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lhozhagensis">
<emphasis italics="true" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="205" pageId="13" pageNumber="204">S. lhozhagensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is different in its usually polycarpic habit, stem 
<quantity box="[814,897,158,185]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="205" unit="cm" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2–5 cm</quantity>
tall, leaf blade narrowly oblanceolate to narrowly oblong, 2–5 × 
<quantity box="[297,403,194,221]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="205" unit="cm" value="0.7" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.4">0.4–1 cm</quantity>
, capitula 5–25, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fujikawa &amp; Ohba" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Liu" baseAuthorityYear="1984" box="[674,812,195,221]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="205" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="conaensis">
<emphasis box="[674,812,195,221]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="205">S. conaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is different in its usually monocarpic habit, stem 12–20(– 30) cm tall, leaf blade linear to narrowly oblanceolate to narrowly oblong, margin sparsely denticulate, 5–17 × 0.5– 2(–3) cm, capitula solitary. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. S. Chen" authorityYear="2014" box="[444,711,266,293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="205" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lhozhagensis">
<emphasis box="[444,711,266,293]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="205">Saussurea lhozhagensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Kitamura (1969: 6)" authorityName="Kitamura" authorityPageNumber="6" authorityYear="1969" box="[910,1269,266,293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="205" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nishiokae">
<emphasis box="[910,1045,266,293]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="205">S. nishiokae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kitamura, S." box="[1052,1269,266,293]" pageId="14" pageNumber="205" pagination="1 - 27" refId="ref7374" refString="Kitamura, S. (1969) Compositae of southeast Asia and Himalayas IV. Acta Phytotaxonomica et Geobotanica 24 (1 - 2): 1 - 27." type="journal article" year="1969">Kitamura (1969: 6)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in its leaf shape and mumerous capitula but differs in its usually polycarpic habit, stem 
<quantity box="[922,1004,302,329]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="205" unit="cm" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2–5 cm</quantity>
tall, leaf blade narrowly oblanceolate to narrowly oblong, margin with 2–4 pairs of teeth, receptacle naked, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kitamura" authorityYear="1969" box="[987,1122,338,365]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="205" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nishiokae">
<emphasis box="[987,1122,338,365]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="205">S. nishiokae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is different in its monocarpic habit, stem 
<quantity box="[267,365,374,401]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.95" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="14" pageNumber="205" unit="cm" value="19.5" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="9.0">9–30 cm</quantity>
tall, leaf blade narrowly elliptic to oblong, margin entire, receptacles densely papillose, papillae ca. 
<quantity box="[175,261,410,437]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="205" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
long. A comparison of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fujikawa &amp; Ohba" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Liu" baseAuthorityYear="1984" box="[523,661,411,437]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="205" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="conaensis">
<emphasis box="[523,661,411,437]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="205">S. conaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. S. Chen" authorityYear="2014" box="[676,849,410,437]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="205" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lhozhagensis">
<emphasis box="[676,849,410,437]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="205">S. lhozhagensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kitamura" authorityYear="1969" box="[903,1038,410,437]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="205" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nishiokae">
<emphasis box="[903,1038,410,437]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="205">S. nishiokae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is given in 
<tableCitation box="[1168,1254,410,436]" captionStart="TABLE 6" captionStartId="14.[136,224,477,501]" captionText="TABLE 6. Comparison of Saussurea conaensis, S. lhozhagensis and S. nishiokae." pageId="14" pageNumber="205">Table 6</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
